Badam is a medium size village located in Badampahar Block of Mayurbhanj district, Orissa with total 110 families residing. The Badam village has population of 467 of which 232 are males while 235 are females as per Population Census 2011.

In Badam village population of children with age 0-6 is 75 which makes up 16.06 % of total population of village. Average Sex Ratio of Badam village is 1013 which is higher than Orissa state average of 979. Child Sex Ratio for the Badam as per census is 1143, higher than Orissa average of 941.

Badam village has lower literacy rate compared to Orissa. In 2011, literacy rate of Badam village was 39.29 % compared to 72.87 % of Orissa. In Badam Male literacy stands at 54.31 % while female literacy rate was 24.10 %.

